description: ONC CIB Port Fault Code bits: 4=Overcurrent; 6=Open Load; 7=Thermal Shut Down; 8=High Accuracy Sense Invalid
ONC CIB Board Fault Code bits: 0=Ground Fault to the Negative Rail; 1=Ground Fault to the Positive Rail; 2=Undervoltage; 3=Overvoltage; 4=Overcurrent; 5=Software Error
Bottom Lock: Sensor ability to see bottom
Current Direction: from North in degree
Defog: Remove fog effect from image
Defog Effect: Amount of defog effect
Detection Ratio: Short to Long Term Average
Count: engineering data, count in thousands
Time: GPS interval time of week
Maximum exposure time of Camera in microsec
ONC CIB Port State: 0=Power Off; 1=Power On; 2=Relay Closed; 3=DCDC Enabled; 4=Fault Detected; 5=Duty Cycle; 6=Check Command
Temperature: air, snow, ice, sea water
UTM Zone: for longitude band, positive north
Wave Direction: wave direction at peak period
Rayfin White Balance: 0=Off, 1=Auto, 2=Aquorea MK2, 3=Aquorea MK3, 4=CloudyDaylight, 5=Daylight, 6=Fluorescent, 7=Incandescent, 8=Manual, 9=Shade, 10=Shallow Water, 11=Twilight
